<div id="Thmexercise1" class="ltx_theorem ltx_theorem_exercise">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_title_theorem"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_theorem"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_bold">Exercise 1</span></span> (Martingales Warm-up).</h6>
<div id="Thmexercise1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Do enough of these exercises to feel comfortable with them.</p>
<ol id="S0.I1" class="ltx_enumerate">
<li id="S0.I1.i1" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">1.</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Assume that <math id="S0.I1.i1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="X_{n}" display="inline"><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> is an integrable <math id="S0.I1.i1.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(\mathcal{F}_{n})" display="inline"><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></math> adapted stochastic
process which is decreasing, i.e.</p>
<table id="S0.EGx1" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex1"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle X_{n+1}\leq X_{n}\quad\text{a.s.}." display="inline"><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>â‰¤</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo mathvariant="italic" separator="true">â€ƒ</mo><mtext>a.s.</mtext></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>
<p class="ltx_p">Prove that <math id="S0.I1.i1.p1.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="X_{n}" display="inline"><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> is a supermartingale.</p>
</div>
<div id="Thmremarkx1" class="ltx_theorem ltx_theorem_remark">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_title_theorem"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_theorem"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_bold">Remark</span></span>.</h6>
<div id="Thmremarkx1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Similarly an adapted increasing process is a submartingale.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="ltx_proof">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_font_italic ltx_title_proof">Solution.</h6>
<div id="S0.I1.i1.p2" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">We simply use the monotonicity of the conditional expectation to
obtain the last property of supermartingales</p>
<table id="S0.EGx2" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex2"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex2.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle\mathbb{E}[X_{n+1}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]" display="inline"><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex2.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle\leq\mathbb{E}[X_{n}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]=X_{n}.\qed" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi></mi><mo>â‰¤</mo><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo>.</mo><mo mathvariant="italic" separator="true">âˆ</mo></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div></li>
<li id="S0.I1.i2" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">2.</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i2.p1" class="ltx_para ltx_noindent">
<p class="ltx_p">Let <math id="S0.I1.i2.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(X_{n})_{n\in\mathbb{N}}" display="inline"><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>â„•</mi></mrow></msub></math>, <math id="S0.I1.i2.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(Y_{n})_{n\in\mathbb{N}}" display="inline"><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>â„•</mi></mrow></msub></math> be <math id="S0.I1.i2.p1.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\mathcal{F}_{n}" display="inline"><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> (sub-)martingales,
prove that</p>
<ol id="S0.I1.I1" class="ltx_enumerate">
<li id="S0.I1.i2.i1" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">(a)</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p"><math id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(X_{n}+Y_{n})_{n\in\mathbb{N}}" display="inline"><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>â„•</mi></mrow></msub></math> is a (sub-)martingale.</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_proof">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_font_italic ltx_title_proof">Solution.</h6>
<div id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p2" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">We have <math id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p2.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\mathbb{E}[|X_{n}+Y_{n}|]\leq\mathbb{E}[|X_{n}|]+\mathbb{E}[|Y_{n}|]&lt;\infty" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>â‰¤</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ</mi></mrow></math> and <math id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p2.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\mathcal{F}_{n}" display="inline"><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>-adapted
follows from the fact that sums of measurable functions are measurable.
What is left to show is</p>
<table id="S0.EGx3" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex3"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex3.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle\mathbb{E}[X_{n+1}+Y_{n+1}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]=\mathbb{E}[X_{n+1%&#10;}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]+\mathbb{E}[Y_{n+1}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]=X_{n}+Y_{n}" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>Y</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>Y</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>
<p class="ltx_p">or the same with <math id="S0.I1.i2.i1.p2.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\geq" display="inline"><mo>â‰¥</mo></math> for submartingales respectively.
âˆ</p>
</div>
</div></li>
<li id="S0.I1.i2.i2" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">(b)</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i2.i2.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p"><math id="S0.I1.i2.i2.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(X_{n}\vee Y_{n})_{n\in\mathbb{N}}" display="inline"><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>âˆ¨</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>â„•</mi></mrow></msub></math> is a submartingale,</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_proof">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_font_italic ltx_title_proof">Solution.</h6>
<div id="S0.I1.i2.i2.p2" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Adapted and integrable is easy to check, and the submartingale property
follows from the monotonicity of conditional expectation</p>
<table id="S0.EGx4" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex4"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex4.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle\mathbb{E}[X_{n+1}\vee Y_{n+1}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]" display="inline"><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>âˆ¨</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>Y</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex4.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle\geq\begin{cases}\mathbb{E}[X_{n+1}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]\geq X_{n%&#10;}&amp;X_{n}\geq Y_{n}\\&#10;\mathbb{E}[Y_{n+1}\,|\,\mathcal{F}_{n}]\geq Y_{n}&amp;Y_{n}\geq X_{n}\end{cases}" display="inline"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>â‰¥</mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mtable columnspacing="5pt" rowspacing="0pt"><mtr><mtd columnalign="left"><mrow><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>â‰¥</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mtd><mtd columnalign="left"><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>â‰¥</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd columnalign="left"><mrow><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msub><mi>Y</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo lspace="2.5pt" rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>â‰¥</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mtd><mtd columnalign="left"><mrow><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>â‰¥</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mtd></mtr></mtable></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
<tbody id="S0.Ex5"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex5.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle=X_{n}\vee Y_{n}.\qed" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>âˆ¨</mo><msub><mi>Y</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo><mo mathvariant="italic" separator="true">âˆ</mo></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div></li>
</ol>
</div></li>
<li id="S0.I1.i3" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">3.</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i3.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Let <math id="S0.I1.i3.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(X_{n})_{n\in\mathbb{N}_{0}}" display="inline"><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><msub><mi>â„•</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></msub></math> be a <math id="S0.I1.i3.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(\mathcal{F}_{n})" display="inline"><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></math>-submartingale. Let <math id="S0.I1.i3.p1.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="T" display="inline"><mi>T</mi></math> be <math id="S0.I1.i3.p1.m4" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(\mathcal{F}_{n})" display="inline"><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></math>-stopping time.</p>
<ol id="S0.I1.I2" class="ltx_enumerate">
<li id="S0.I1.i3.i1" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">(a)</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Suppose that <math id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(X_{n})_{n\in\mathbb{N}_{0}}" display="inline"><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><msub><mi>â„•</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></msub></math> is bounded and <math id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="T" display="inline"><mi>T</mi></math> is a.s.
finite (the meaning is different from â€<math id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p1.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="T" display="inline"><mi>T</mi></math> is a.s.Â boundedâ€!). Prove
that <math id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p1.m4" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\mathbb{E}[X_{0}]\leq\mathbb{E}[X_{T}]&lt;\infty" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>â‰¤</mo><mrow><mi>ğ”¼</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>T</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ</mi></mrow></math>.</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_proof">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_font_italic ltx_title_proof">Solution.</h6>
<div id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p2" class="ltx_para ltx_noindent">
<p class="ltx_p">Since <math id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p2.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="T&lt;\infty" display="inline"><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ</mi></mrow></math> a.s. we have</p>
<table id="S0.EGx5" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex6"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex6.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle X_{T}=\lim_{n\to\infty}X_{T\wedge n}=\lim_{n\to\infty}X^{T}_{n}" display="inline"><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mrow><munder><mo movablelimits="false">lim</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>â†’</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ</mi></mrow></munder><mo>â¡</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>âˆ§</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><munder><mo movablelimits="false">lim</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>â†’</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ</mi></mrow></munder><mo>â¡</mo><msubsup><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>T</mi></msubsup></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>
<p class="ltx_p">where <math id="S0.I1.i3.i1.p2.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="X^{T}=(X_{T\wedge n})_{n\in\mathbb{N}}" display="inline"><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>âˆ§</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>â„•</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></math> is a bounded submartingale,
because</p>
<ul id="S0.I2" class="ltx_itemize">
<li id="S0.I2.i1" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">â€¢</span> 
<div id="S0.I2.i1.p1" class="ltx_para ltx_noindent">
<p class="ltx_p">as <math id="S0.I2.i1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\mathcal{F}_{n\wedge T}\subseteq\mathcal{F}_{n}" display="inline"><mrow><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆ§</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub><mo>âŠ†</mo><msub><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">â„±</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></math> as <math id="S0.I2.i1.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n\wedge T\leq n" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>âˆ§</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mo>â‰¤</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></math>
therefore <math id="S0.I2.i1.p1.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="X^{T}" display="inline"><msup><mi>X</mi><mi>T</mi></msup></math> is adapted</p>
</div></li>
