</div>
<div id="Thmhintx1" class="ltx_theorem ltx_theorem_hint">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_title_theorem"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_theorem"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_bold">Hint</span></span>.</h6>
<div id="Thmhintx1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Compare this with statements about martingales in the lectures and
use the bounded stopping time <math id="Thmhintx1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="T\wedge M" display="inline"><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant="normal">âˆ§</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow></math> for some constant <math id="Thmhintx1.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="M\in\mathbb{N}" display="inline"><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo mathvariant="normal">âˆˆ</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi></mrow></math> and the dominated convergence theorem.</span></p>
